In Tombstone Weekly Epitaph, issue January 10, 1915, there's a cronicle of events during 1914 in México:
&quot;April 21.--American marines captured part of Vera Cruz after a fight in which four Americans were killed and twenty-one wounded and about 200 Mexicans were killed.  Read Admiral Badger with five ships arrived at Veracruz.&quot;
